title <size:18>EC2 Instance Discount System - Class Diagram (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "Customer launches t3.large in us-east-1. System picks best discount: Reserved 3yr > Savings Plan > Spot > On-Demand."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE — PricingService
' ====================================================================
class PricingService <<Facade>> {
    - basePriceRegistry : BasePriceRegistry
    - discountEngine : DiscountEngine
    - usageTracker : UsageTracker
    - spotMarket : SpotPriceService
    --
    + calculatePrice(instance, customer) : PriceBreakdown
    + getBestDiscount(instance, customer) : DiscountStrategy
    + getAvailableDiscounts(instance, customer) : List<DiscountStrategy>
    + estimateMonthlyCost(instances, customer) : PriceBreakdown
}

note top of PricingService #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "Customer launches an EC2 instance.
    PricingService is the **Facade** — it
    coordinates base pricing, discount
    selection, usage tracking, and spot
    market. Returns a PriceBreakdown."
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: EC2 INSTANCE MODEL
' ====================================================================
class EC2Instance {
    - instanceId : String
    - type : InstanceType
    - size : InstanceSize
    - region : Region
    - os : OperatingSystem
    - state : InstanceState
    - launchedAt : LocalDateTime
    --
    + getHourlyBasePrice() : double
    + isRunning() : boolean
}

enum InstanceType {
    T2_GENERAL
    T3_GENERAL
    M5_GENERAL
    C5_COMPUTE
    R5_MEMORY
    P3_GPU
}

enum InstanceSize {
    NANO
    MICRO
    SMALL
    MEDIUM
    LARGE
    XLARGE
    TWOXLARGE
}

enum Region {
    US_EAST_1
    US_WEST_2
    EU_WEST_1
    AP_SOUTH_1
    AP_SOUTHEAST_1
}

enum OperatingSystem {
    LINUX
    WINDOWS
    RHEL
    SUSE
}

enum InstanceState {
    RUNNING
    STOPPED
    TERMINATED
}

note top of EC2Instance #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - What are we pricing?**
    "An EC2Instance has a type (t3, m5, c5),
    size (micro to 2xlarge), region,
    and OS. Each combination has a
    different base hourly rate."
    "Pure model, no pricing logic." **(SRP)**
end note

EC2Instance --> InstanceType
EC2Instance --> InstanceSize
EC2Instance --> Region
EC2Instance --> OperatingSystem
EC2Instance --> InstanceState


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: CUSTOMER + USAGE
' ====================================================================
class Customer {
    - customerId : String
    - name : String
    - accountType : AccountType
    - reservations : List<Reservation>
    - savingsPlans : List<SavingsPlan>
    --
    + getAccountType() : AccountType
    + getActiveReservations() : List<Reservation>
    + getActiveSavingsPlans() : List<SavingsPlan>
}

enum AccountType {
    INDIVIDUAL
    STARTUP
    ENTERPRISE
    GOVERNMENT
}

class UsageTracker {
    - instanceHours : Map<String, Long>
    - monthlySpend : Map<String, Double>
    --
    + getTotalInstanceHours(customerId) : long
    + getMonthlySpend(customerId) : double
    + getRunningInstanceCount(customerId) : int
    + recordUsage(customerId, instance, hours) : void
}

note top of Customer #C8E6C9
    **STEP 3 - Who is being charged?**
    "Customer has account type (Individual,
    Enterprise, Government), active
    reservations, and savings plans.
    **UsageTracker** records total hours
    and monthly spend — needed for
    volume-based discounts."
end note

Customer --> AccountType
PricingService --> UsageTracker : tracks usage >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: BASE PRICE REGISTRY
' ====================================================================
class BasePriceRegistry {
    - prices : Map<PriceKey, Double>
    --
    + getHourlyRate(type, size, region, os) : double
    + registerPrice(key, rate) : void
}

class PriceKey {
    - type : InstanceType
    - size : InstanceSize
    - region : Region
    - os : OperatingSystem
}

note bottom of BasePriceRegistry #C8E6C9
    **STEP 4 - Base price lookup.**
    "Before any discount, what's the list price?
    BasePriceRegistry maps (type+size+region+OS)
    to an hourly rate. Example: t3.large /
    us-east-1 / Linux = $0.0832/hr.
    All discounts are applied ON TOP of this."
end note

BasePriceRegistry --> PriceKey : indexed by >
PricingService --> BasePriceRegistry : looks up >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: DISCOUNT STRATEGY — Core Pattern (Strategy)
' ====================================================================
interface DiscountStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + calculatePrice(basePrice, instance, customer) : double
    + getDiscountPercent(instance, customer) : double
    + getDiscountName() : String
    + isEligible(instance, customer) : boolean
}

class OnDemandPricing <<ConcreteStrategy>> {
    --
    + calculatePrice(basePrice, instance, customer) : double
    + getDiscountPercent(instance, customer) : double
    + isEligible(instance, customer) : boolean
}

class ReservedInstanceDiscount <<ConcreteStrategy>> {
    - term : ReservationTerm
    - paymentOption : PaymentOption
    --
    + calculatePrice(basePrice, instance, customer) : double
    + getDiscountPercent(instance, customer) : double
    + isEligible(instance, customer) : boolean
}

class SavingsPlanDiscount <<ConcreteStrategy>> {
    - commitmentPerHour : double
    - term : ReservationTerm
    --
    + calculatePrice(basePrice, instance, customer) : double
    + getDiscountPercent(instance, customer) : double
    + isEligible(instance, customer) : boolean
}

class SpotInstanceDiscount <<ConcreteStrategy>> {
    - spotPriceService : SpotPriceService
    --
    + calculatePrice(basePrice, instance, customer) : double
    + getDiscountPercent(instance, customer) : double
    + isEligible(instance, customer) : boolean
    + getCurrentSpotPrice(type, size, region) : double
}

class VolumeDiscount <<ConcreteStrategy>> {
    - usageTracker : UsageTracker
    - tiers : List<VolumeTier>
    --
    + calculatePrice(basePrice, instance, customer) : double
    + getDiscountPercent(instance, customer) : double
    + isEligible(instance, customer) : boolean
}

class EnterpriseDiscount <<ConcreteStrategy>> {
    - negotiatedRate : double
    --
    + calculatePrice(basePrice, instance, customer) : double
    + getDiscountPercent(instance, customer) : double
    + isEligible(instance, customer) : boolean
}

note top of DiscountStrategy #FFE0B2
    **STEP 5 - The core design. (KEY STEP)**
    "One interface: calculatePrice(). Each discount
    type is a **Strategy** — pluggable, independent."

    "**OnDemand**: 0% off (pay-as-you-go).
    **Reserved**: 30-60% off (1yr/3yr commit).
    **SavingsPlan**: 20-40% off ($/hr commit).
    **Spot**: up to 90% off (interruptible).
    **Volume**: tiered % off (by total hours).
    **Enterprise**: custom negotiated rate."

    "isEligible() checks if customer qualifies.
    Add FreeTrialDiscount? One new class."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP, LSP**
end note

DiscountStrategy <|.. OnDemandPricing
DiscountStrategy <|.. ReservedInstanceDiscount
DiscountStrategy <|.. SavingsPlanDiscount
DiscountStrategy <|.. SpotInstanceDiscount
DiscountStrategy <|.. VolumeDiscount
DiscountStrategy <|.. EnterpriseDiscount


' ====================================================================
'  SUPPORTING: Reservation terms, Volume tiers
' ====================================================================
class Reservation {
    - reservationId : String
    - instanceType : InstanceType
    - instanceSize : InstanceSize
    - term : ReservationTerm
    - paymentOption : PaymentOption
    - startDate : LocalDate
    - endDate : LocalDate
    --
    + isActive() : boolean
    + coversInstance(instance) : boolean
}

enum ReservationTerm {
    ONE_YEAR
    THREE_YEAR
}

enum PaymentOption {
    ALL_UPFRONT
    PARTIAL_UPFRONT
    NO_UPFRONT
}

class SavingsPlan {
    - planId : String
    - commitmentPerHour : double
    - term : ReservationTerm
    - startDate : LocalDate
    --
    + isActive() : boolean
    + getRemainingCommitment() : double
}

class VolumeTier {
    - minHours : long
    - maxHours : long
    - discountPercent : double
}

Reservation --> ReservationTerm
Reservation --> PaymentOption
Customer --> Reservation : holds >
Customer --> SavingsPlan : holds >
ReservedInstanceDiscount --> Reservation : checks >
SavingsPlanDiscount --> SavingsPlan : checks >
VolumeDiscount --> VolumeTier : uses tiers >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: DISCOUNT DECORATOR — Stacking Discounts
' ====================================================================
abstract class DiscountDecorator <<Decorator>> {
    # wrapped : DiscountStrategy
    --
    + calculatePrice(basePrice, instance, customer) : double
    + getDiscountName() : String
}

class LoyaltyDiscountDecorator {
    - loyaltyPercent : double
    - minAccountAgeDays : int
    --
    + calculatePrice(basePrice, instance, customer) : double
    + isEligible(instance, customer) : boolean
}

class PromoCodeDecorator {
    - promoCode : String
    - promoPercent : double
    - validUntil : LocalDate
    --
    + calculatePrice(basePrice, instance, customer) : double
    + isEligible(instance, customer) : boolean
}

note bottom of DiscountDecorator #FFCDD2
    **STEP 6 - Stack discounts.**
    "Customer has Reserved 3yr + Loyalty bonus.
    **Decorator Pattern** — wraps a base strategy
    and adds another layer on top."

    "new LoyaltyDecorator(
      new ReservedInstanceDiscount(3yr, allUpfront)
    )"

    "Reserved gives 60% off, Loyalty adds 5% more.
    PromoCode adds temporary extra discount.
    Composable without modifying any strategy."
    **Pattern: Decorator | OCP, SRP**
end note

DiscountStrategy <|.. DiscountDecorator
DiscountDecorator o--> DiscountStrategy : wraps >
DiscountDecorator <|-- LoyaltyDiscountDecorator
DiscountDecorator <|-- PromoCodeDecorator


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: DISCOUNT ENGINE — Selects Best Strategy
' ====================================================================
class DiscountEngine {
    - strategies : List<DiscountStrategy>
    --
    + findBestDiscount(instance, customer) : DiscountStrategy
    + findAllEligible(instance, customer) : List<DiscountStrategy>
    + registerStrategy(strategy) : void
}

note bottom of DiscountEngine #D1C4E9
    **STEP 7 - Pick the best discount.**
    "Multiple discounts may apply. DiscountEngine
    iterates all registered strategies, filters
    by isEligible(), computes price for each,
    and returns the cheapest option."

    "This is the **orchestrator** — decoupled
    from individual strategy logic."
    **(SRP, OCP)**
end note

DiscountEngine o--> DiscountStrategy : evaluates >
PricingService --> DiscountEngine : uses >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: SPOT PRICE — Observer Pattern
' ====================================================================
class SpotPriceService {
    - currentPrices : Map<PriceKey, Double>
    - observers : List<SpotPriceObserver>
    --
    + getCurrentPrice(type, size, region) : double
    + updatePrice(key, newPrice) : void
    + registerObserver(obs) : void
    - notifyObservers(key, oldPrice, newPrice) : void
}

interface SpotPriceObserver <<Observer>> {
    + onPriceChange(key, oldPrice, newPrice) : void
}

class SpotInterruptionHandler {
    --
    + onPriceChange(key, oldPrice, newPrice) : void
}

class CustomerAlertObserver {
    --
    + onPriceChange(key, oldPrice, newPrice) : void
}

note bottom of SpotPriceObserver #B2EBF2
    **STEP 8 - Spot prices fluctuate.**
    "Spot pricing changes with market demand.
    **Observer Pattern** — when spot price
    changes, observers react:
    **InterruptionHandler**: terminates instances
    if price exceeds customer's max bid.
    **CustomerAlert**: notifies of price changes."
    **Pattern: Observer | OCP, SRP**
end note

SpotPriceObserver <|.. SpotInterruptionHandler
SpotPriceObserver <|.. CustomerAlertObserver
SpotPriceService --> SpotPriceObserver : notifies >
SpotInstanceDiscount --> SpotPriceService : reads >
PricingService --> SpotPriceService


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 9: PRICE BREAKDOWN — Result Object
' ====================================================================
class PriceBreakdown {
    - baseHourlyRate : double
    - discountApplied : String
    - discountPercent : double
    - finalHourlyRate : double
    - estimatedMonthly : double
    - appliedStrategies : List<String>
    --
    + getBaseRate() : double
    + getFinalRate() : double
    + getSavings() : double
    + getSavingsPercent() : double
    + toString() : String
}

note bottom of PriceBreakdown #C8E6C9
    **STEP 9 - Transparent result.**
    "PriceBreakdown shows the customer:
    Base: $0.0832/hr
    Discount: Reserved 3yr All-Upfront (60%)
    + Loyalty (5%)
    Final: $0.0316/hr
    Monthly estimate: $22.75
    Total savings: 62%"
end note

PricingService --> PriceBreakdown : returns >


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "Customer launches t3.large. PricingService looks up
    base rate ($0.0832/hr), DiscountEngine finds all eligible strategies,
    picks cheapest: Reserved 3yr All-Upfront (60% off). LoyaltyDecorator
    adds 5% more. Spot prices fluctuate and Observer notifies.
    Result: transparent PriceBreakdown."

    "**5 patterns**: Strategy (6 discount types), Decorator (stacking),
    Observer (spot prices), Facade (PricingService).
    Add any new discount = one new class. System untouched."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= SOLID |
    | 1 | Customer calls PricingService.calculatePrice() | Facade | SRP, DIP |
    | 2 | EC2Instance: type + size + region + OS | -- | SRP |
    | 3 | Customer: account type, reservations, savings plans | -- | SRP |
    | 4 | BasePriceRegistry: lookup hourly rate by (type,size,region,os) | -- | SRP |
    | 5 | 6 discount strategies: OnDemand, Reserved, Spot, SavingsPlan, Volume, Enterprise | Strategy | OCP, DIP, LSP |
    | 6 | Stack discounts: Loyalty + PromoCode wrap base strategy | Decorator | OCP, SRP |
    | 7 | DiscountEngine picks cheapest eligible strategy | -- | SRP, OCP |
    | 8 | Spot prices fluctuate, observers react (interrupt, alert) | Observer | OCP, SRP |
    | 9 | PriceBreakdown: base, discount, final, monthly estimate | -- | SRP |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Pricing** = Steps 4-7 | **Spot Market** = Step 8 | **Result** = Step 9 |  |
endlegend

@enduml
